**Privacy Policy for Budget Tracker**

**Effective Date:** March 3, 2026

[ZappsDev] ("we," "us," or "our") operates the Budget Tracker mobile application (the "Service"). We are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your choices regarding your information.

By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

### 1. Information We Collect

Our primary goal is to provide you with a secure and efficient budgeting experience. The information we handle can be broken down into two categories:

**a) Information You Provide**

All financial data you enter into the App is stored **locally on your device**. We do not have access to this information. This includes:
*   **Transactions:** Details about your income and expenses, such as amounts, descriptions, categories, and dates.
*   **Financial Goals:** Information about your savings or debt repayment goals.
*   **Accounts and Categories:** Names for different budget accounts (a premium feature) and any custom categories you create.

**b) Information Collected Automatically**

To support the App's functionality, we and our third-party partners may collect certain information automatically:

*   **Advertising Data:** Our app uses Google AdMob to display advertisements. To make these ads relevant, AdMob may collect data such as your device's advertising ID, IP address, and information about your interactions with ads. [1, 4, 6] You can opt out of personalized advertising through your device's settings.
*   **In-App Purchase and Validation Data:** When you purchase the Premium version, we process the transaction through the platform's app store (Google Play or Apple App Store). To validate purchases and prevent fraud, we may securely send transaction receipts to a validation service. This process may include device information such as the device model, operating system version, and a hashed, non-reversible device fingerprint. This data is used for support, analytics, and fraud detection.
*   **Usage and Diagnostics Data:** We may collect anonymous data about how you interact with the app to identify crashes and improve our Service. [2] This includes information like device type, OS version, and crash logs. [5]

### 2. How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information for the following purposes:

*   **To Provide and Maintain the Service:** Your locally stored financial data is used to power all the core features of the app, such as displaying your balance, transactions, and charts.
*   **To Provide Premium Features:** To process and restore your one-time purchase for premium features.
*   **To Display Advertisements:** To support the free version of the app, we use Google AdMob to show ads. [3]
*   **To Improve the App:** We analyze anonymous usage and crash data to understand how our app is used, fix bugs, and enhance the user experience. [2]
*   **To Prevent Fraud:** We use receipt validation to ensure the integrity of in-app purchases.

### 3. Data Storage and Security

Your personal financial data is stored exclusively on your device's local storage. If you delete the app, this data may be permanently removed.

The premium feature to export your data as an Excel or PDF file saves the file to a location on your device that you control.

We take reasonable measures to protect your information, but please be aware that no method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

### 4. Third-Party Services

We use the following third-party services, which have their own privacy policies:

*   **Google AdMob & Google Play Services:** Used for displaying ads and providing core device services.
    *   [Google Privacy Policy](https://policies.google.com/privacy)
*   **Apple App Store:** Used for processing In-App Purchases on iOS devices.
    *   [Apple Privacy Policy](https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/en-ww/)
*   **Third-Party CDNs:** We use services like Google Fonts and Cloudflare to deliver fonts and other assets, which may collect technical data like your IP address as part of their normal operation.

### 5. Your Privacy Choices

*   **Managing Your Data:** You have full control over the financial data you enter. You can add, edit, or delete any transaction or clear all data for an account from within the app's settings.
*   **Opting Out of Personalized Ads:** You can limit ad tracking by adjusting the settings on your device.
    *   **On iOS:** Go to Settings > Privacy & Security > Tracking.
    *   **On Android:** Go to Settings > Google > Ads > Delete advertising ID.
*   **In-App Purchases:** You can manage your in-app purchases and subscriptions through your Google Play or Apple ID account settings.

### 6. Children's Privacy

This Service is not intended for use by anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. If we become aware that a child has provided us with personal information, we will take steps to remove such information.

### 7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy within the app. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

